tspan.tspan: Reverse engineering like a pro or at least like someone who finaly read the #$!@ing manual.
Welcome to the Radare2 command-line jungle where cryptic spells (axt, px, s @0x...) slice
through binaries, helping you script your way through reverse-engineering quests. Whether
you're a seasoned reverse engineer, a curious hacker, or just someone who likes to poke
around things you probably shouldnt, this book is for you.
The Official Radare2 Book helps you explore one of the most powerful and uniquely odd
tools in the binary analysis scene. Learn how to:
Tame the Radare2 CLI (yes, this book explains all the dots, slashes and !magic)
Debug, patch, and break stuff sometimes on purpose
Script your way out of anything with ESIL, r2pipe and your favorite scripting language
Explore visual mode without losing your mind
Play with crackmes, emulators, and even build your own combat bots for r2wars
Packed with examples, field-tested tips and a few sharp comments, this book is less of a
handbook and more of a survival guide.
May cause increased curiosity and a mild addiction to disassembling things.
